      • setToken

        public void setToken(java.lang.String token)
        Set the result token. The token is used to identify an internal system object that was created to process the request. Examples are trouble ticket id, or the id of a workflow process. In some systems this can be used to poll for status.

      • setRetryInterval

        public void setRetryInterval(int seconds)
        Set the retry interval. This is the optional preferred amount of time to wait before the request is retried. The value is in seconds. This is ignored unless status is Retry.

      • getRetryInterval

        public int getRetryInterval()
        This is the optional preferred amount of time to wait before the request is retried. The value is in seconds. This is ignored unless status is Retry.
        Returns:
        the retry interval.

      • setObject

        public void setObject(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> obj)
        Set the result object. This may be optionally returned by the connector in the result stored within a Request. When this is returned it will contain all of the attributes of the updated object, which can include things that were not in the request. This can then be used by the caller to refresh an external model rather than waiting for the next aggregation.
